reviews.review_text: Monumental This is a spectacular show and the sound is great throughout. As always, thank you tapers! I'd give it 5 stars but for the wailing banshee in the otherworldly Playin'. There are many highlights, but check out the guitar solo from Mars in Candyman-out there! Nice China-Rider transition as well as an early 'kinda different'"Roses." Sweet, jammin Cumberland. As for the 29 minute Dark Star segueing into a deep, powerful Dew, well, "thank you" just seems so insufficient. Nice mini Spanish Jam in DS, too. Bobby goes ballistic in the NFA closer, then a rare mid-70s Baby Blue winds it up. Cheers to yer ears!

Excellent Quality and Perfomance Great show, the China Cat into Rider is absolutley amazing. 

Goin down the road is standard for the '74 era, with the we bid u goodnight instrumental after it.

Not a bad thing i can say about this show...
